programme.desc:
In the premiere episode of Modern Homestead, Janna Breslin and Evan DeMarco take the plunge into a world they've never known before, as they embark on a journey that promises to challenge their limits, expand their horizons, and redefine their very notions of homesteading. What begins as a bold venture to buy 120 acres in the picturesque Tennessee landscape quickly transforms into an eye-opening experience that neither of them could have anticipated.
The episode kicks off with excitement and a sense of adventure as Janna and Evan, an unlikely pair consisting of a cover model and a scientist, reveal their audacious plan to create a thriving homestead capable of withstanding even the most unexpected challenges - including a potential zombie apocalypse. Armed with enthusiasm and a determination to master the art of self-sufficiency, they set out to build their dream oasis where they will source their own water, grow their own food, generate energy, and construct their own shelter.
However, as the saying goes, reality often has other plans. What Janna and Evan initially perceive as a straightforward path to their modern homesteading vision takes an unexpected turn. As they explore their new purchase, they encounter challenges that leave them both baffled and humbled. The land they imagined to be a canvas of endless possibilities presents them with a unique set of obstacles they hadn't foreseen.
Amidst the breathtaking beauty of the Tennessee landscape, the duo faces unexpected revelations. The landscape itself is both enchanting and unpredictable, with its own stories etched into every rock and tree. With each twist and turn, Janna and Evan's perceptions of their journey shift, and they find themselves relying on each other's strengths more than ever before.
As they dive deeper into their new reality, the couple discovers that their homesteading adventure is about more than just mastering survival skills; it's about embracing the unknown, learning from failures, and celebrating triumphs no matter how small. The episode captures the candid moments of frustration, laughter, and perseverance as they navigate through the challenges of homesteading.

In the second episode of The Modern Homestead, Janna and Evan's journey gets off to a chaotic start when Janna wakes up with something very dangerous in her hair.
With Janna's hair emergency as a wake-up call, Evan swings into action and calls in the experts. They bring in a food security systems designer and a homesteading expert to help them navigate the complexities of their new life.
Simultaneously, the couple recognizes the pressing need to transform their cabin into a more safe, functional and comfortable space. This includes building a much-needed bathroom for those moments when Evan has a bit too much chili.
Episode two brings laughs, excitement and and the recognition that building the Modern Homestead might not be as easy as they thought,
